  "version": "2.1.0",
  "runs": [
    {
      "tool": {
        "driver": {
          "name": "Tachi",
          "semanticVersion": "1.1",
          "informationUri": "https://github.com/tachi-org/tachi",
          "supportedTaxonomies": [
            { "name": "OWASP", "index": 0 },
            { "name": "CWE", "index": 1 }
          ],
          "rules": [
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/spoofing",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Identity spoofing threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker assumes the identity of another entity — user, service, or system component — undermining authentication guarantees and enabling unauthorized actions under a trusted identity." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authentication mechanisms, credential storage, session management, and service-to-service identity verification for spoofing vulnerabilities.",
                "markdown": "## Detection Guidance\n\nReview the following for spoofing vulnerabilities:\n- Authentication mechanisms at entry points (MFA, password policies)\n- Session token management (lifetime, binding, rotation)\n- Service-to-service authentication (mTLS, signed JWTs)\n- Federated identity configuration (OAuth/OIDC state parameters)\n\n## Framework References\n- [OWASP A07:2021 — Identification and Authentication Failures](https://owasp.org/Top10/A07_2021-Identification_and_Authentication_Failures/)\n- [CWE-287: Improper Authentication](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/287.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1078: Valid Accounts"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "spoofing", "authentication", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                {
                  "target": { "id": "A07", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                },
                {
                  "target": { "id": "CWE-287", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/tampering",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Data tampering threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker modifies data, code, or configuration without authorization, violating integrity guarantees and causing systems to operate on corrupted inputs or persist falsified records." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review input validation, message integrity, data flow encryption, configuration management, and write-path access controls for tampering vulnerabilities.",
                "markdown": "## Detection Guidance\n\nReview the following for tampering vulnerabilities:\n- Input validation and sanitization on all write paths\n- Message integrity protection (HMAC, digital signatures) on inter-service communication\n- Configuration integrity verification (checksums, drift detection)\n- Data store access controls and audit trails\n\n## Framework References\n- [OWASP A08:2021 — Software and Data Integrity Failures](https://owasp.org/Top10/A08_2021-Software_and_Data_Integrity_Failures/)\n- [CWE-345: Insufficient Verification of Data Authenticity](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/345.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1565: Data Manipulation"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "tampering", "integrity", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                {
                  "target": { "id": "A08", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                },
                {
                  "target": { "id": "CWE-345", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/repudiation",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Repudiation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where a user or system can deny having performed an action and the system lacks sufficient evidence to prove otherwise, undermining accountability, forensic investigation, and compliance obligations." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review audit logging coverage, log integrity protection, non-repudiation controls, and timestamp management for repudiation vulnerabilities.",
                "markdown": "## Detection Guidance\n\nReview the following for repudiation vulnerabilities:\n- Audit log coverage for security-sensitive operations\n- Log detail sufficiency (actor identity, timestamp, before/after state)\n- Log integrity protection (append-only storage, cryptographic chaining)\n- Non-repudiation mechanisms (digital signatures, TLS client certificates)\n\n## Framework References\n- [OWASP A09:2021 — Security Logging and Monitoring Failures](https://owasp.org/Top10/A09_2021-Security_Logging_and_Monitoring_Failures/)\n- [CWE-778: Insufficient Logging](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/778.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1070: Indicator Removal"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "repudiation", "logging", "accountability", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                {
                  "target": { "id": "A09", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                },
                {
                  "target": { "id": "CWE-778", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/information-disclosure",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Information disclosure threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where sensitive information is exposed to unauthorized parties through direct data leaks, verbose error messages, side-channel observations, or insufficient access controls on stored data." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review error handling, API response filtering, data-at-rest encryption, data-in-transit protection, and access controls for information disclosure vulnerabilities.",
                "markdown": "## Detection Guidance\n\nReview the following for information disclosure vulnerabilities:\n- Error message content (stack traces, connection strings, file paths)\n- API response filtering (excessive data, internal metadata)\n- Data-at-rest encryption and access controls\n- Data-in-transit encryption (TLS on all channels)\n\n## Framework References\n- [OWASP A01:2021 — Broken Access Control](https://owasp.org/Top10/A01_2021-Broken_Access_Control/)\n- [CWE-200: Exposure of Sensitive Information](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/200.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1005: Data from Local System"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "information-disclosure", "data-exposure", "confidentiality", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                {
                  "target": { "id": "A01", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                },
                {
                  "target": { "id": "CWE-200", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/denial-of-service",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Denial of service threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker degrades or eliminates system availability through resource exhaustion, flooding, algorithmic complexity exploitation, or cascading dependency failures." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review rate limiting, resource caps, connection pool management, timeout configuration, and circuit breaker patterns for denial of service vulnerabilities.",
                "markdown": "## Detection Guidance\n\nReview the following for denial of service vulnerabilities:\n- Rate limiting on public-facing endpoints\n- Request size and complexity limits\n- Connection pool and timeout configuration\n- Circuit breaker patterns for external dependencies\n\n## Framework References\n- [OWASP A05:2021 — Security Misconfiguration](https://owasp.org/Top10/A05_2021-Security_Misconfiguration/)\n- [CWE-400: Uncontrolled Resource Consumption](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/400.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1499: Endpoint Denial of Service"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "denial-of-service", "availability", "rate-limiting", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                {
                  "target": { "id": "A05", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                },
                {
                  "target": { "id": "CWE-400", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/stride/elevation-of-privilege",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "Privilege escalation threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats where an attacker gains higher privileges than authorized, performing actions reserved for administrators, accessing other users' resources, or bypassing access control boundaries." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review authorization mechanisms, role-based access controls, privilege boundaries, and function-level access controls for elevation of privilege vulnerabilities.",
                "markdown": "## Detection Guidance\n\nReview the following for privilege escalation vulnerabilities:\n- Authorization checks on all API endpoints\n- Role-based access control enforcement\n- Function-level access control on administrative operations\n- Least privilege enforcement on service accounts\n\n## Framework References\n- [OWASP A01:2021 — Broken Access Control](https://owasp.org/Top10/A01_2021-Broken_Access_Control/)\n- [CWE-269: Improper Privilege Management](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/269.html)\n- MITRE ATT&CK T1548: Abuse Elevation Control Mechanism"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "stride", "elevation-of-privilege", "authorization", "access-control", "owasp", "cwe"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                {
                  "target": { "id": "A01", "toolComponent": { "name": "OWASP" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                },
                {
                  "target": { "id": "CWE-269", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/agentic-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "AI agent autonomy and misuse threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats from autonomous agent systems operating with insufficient constraints on decision-making, action scope, or operational boundaries, including unauthorized tool invocation, capability escalation, and tool poisoning attacks." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review agent autonomy constraints, tool access controls, human-in-the-loop gates, and tool chain policies for agentic threat vulnerabilities.",
                "markdown": "## Detection Guidance\n\nReview the following for agentic threat vulnerabilities:\n- Agent termination constraints (iteration limits, timeouts, cost caps)\n- Tool access controls and per-agent capability scoping\n- Human-in-the-loop approval gates for consequential actions\n- Tool chain policies evaluating composite effects\n\n## Framework References\n- [OWASP Agentic Security Initiative (ASI)](https://owasp.org/www-project-agentic-security-initiative/)\n- MITRE ATLAS: Abuse of AI Agent Capabilities\n- [CWE-693: Protection Mechanism Failure](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/693.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "agentic", "autonomy", "tool-use", "mcp", "owasp"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                {
                  "target": { "id": "CWE-693", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "id": "tachi/ai/llm-threats",
              "shortDescription": { "text": "LLM-specific threats" },
              "fullDescription": { "text": "Threats specific to Large Language Model integrations including prompt injection, data poisoning of RAG pipelines, model theft through systematic querying, and system prompt extraction attacks." },
              "help": {
                "text": "Review prompt handling, RAG pipeline integrity, output filtering, and model API access controls for LLM-specific vulnerabilities.",
                "markdown": "## Detection Guidance\n\nReview the following for LLM-specific vulnerabilities:\n- Prompt boundary enforcement (system vs user content separation)\n- Input classification for adversarial prompt patterns\n- RAG pipeline content validation and provenance tracking\n- Output filtering for system prompt leakage\n- Model API rate limiting and query budget controls\n\n## Framework References\n- [OWASP LLM Top 10 v2025](https://genai.owasp.org/)\n- OWASP LLM01:2025 — Prompt Injection\n- OWASP LLM03:2025 — Supply Chain Vulnerabilities\n- OWASP LLM10:2025 — Model Theft\n- [CWE-74: Improper Neutralization of Special Elements in Output](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/74.html)"
              },
              "properties": {
                "tags": ["security", "ai", "llm", "prompt-injection", "data-poisoning", "model-theft", "owasp"],
                "security-severity": "9.0"
              },
              "relationships": [
                {
                  "target": { "id": "CWE-74", "toolComponent": { "name": "CWE" } },
                  "kinds": ["relevant"]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        }
      },
